5. Control Plane (Master Node)

Manages cluster operations.

Components:

API Server
Scheduler
Controller Manager
etcd
6. API Server

Main entry point of Kubernetes.

Handles:

kubectl requests
REST API communication
7. etcd

Key-value database storing cluster data.

Stores:

Configuration
Cluster state
8. Scheduler

Decides which node runs a pod.

9. Controller Manager

Maintains desired cluster state.

Example:

Restart failed pods automatically
Worker Node Components
10. Kubelet

Agent running on each worker node.

Responsible for:

Managing pods
Communicating with API Server
11. Kube Proxy

Handles networking between pods/services.
